                   ,trip_id = ride_id
                   ,bikeid = rideable_type
                   ,start_time = started_at 
                   ,end_time = ended_at
                   ,from_station_name = start_station_name 
                   ,from_station_id = start_station_id
                   ,to_station_name = end_station_name 
                   ,to_station_id = end_station_id
                   ,usertype = member_casual))

Trip_Apr20 <-  mutate(Trip_Apr20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                   ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id)) 
Trip_May20 <-  mutate(Trip_May20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id)) 
Trip_Jun20 <-  mutate(Trip_Jun20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id)) 
Trip_Jul20 <-  mutate(Trip_Jul20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Aug20 <-  mutate(Trip_Aug20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Sep20 <-  mutate(Trip_Sep20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Oct20 <-  mutate(Trip_Oct20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Nov20 <-  mutate(Trip_Nov20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Dec20 <-  mutate(Trip_Dec20, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Jan21 <-  mutate(Trip_Jan21, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Feb21 <-  mutate(Trip_Feb21, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))
Trip_Mar21 <-  mutate(Trip_Mar21, from_station_id = as.character(from_station_id)
                      ,to_station_id = as.character(to_station_id))

# Stack individual quarter's data frames into one big data frame
all_trips <- bind_rows(Trip_Apr20, Trip_May20, Trip_Jun20, Trip_Jul20, Trip_Aug20, Trip_Sep20, Trip_Oct20, Trip_Nov20, Trip_Dec20, Trip_Jan21, 
                       Trip_Feb21, Trip_Mar21)

#Remove unused column
all_trips <- all_trips %>%
  select(-c(start_lat, start_lng, end_lat, end_lng))

# Add columns that list the date, month, day, and year of each ride
# This will allow us to aggregate ride data for each month, day, or year ... before completing these operations we could only aggregate at the ride level
all_trips$date <- as.Date(all_trips$start_time) #The default format is yyyy-mm-dd
all_trips$month <- format(as.Date(all_trips$date), "%m")
all_trips$day <- format(as.Date(all_trips$date), "%d")
all_trips$year <- format(as.Date(all_trips$date), "%Y")
all_trips$day_of_week <- format(as.Date(all_trips$date), "%A")

# Add a "ride_length" calculation to all_trips (in seconds)
all_trips$ride_length <- difftime(all_trips$end_time,all_trips$start_time)

# analyze ridership data by type and weekday
all_trips_v2 %>% 
  mutate(weekday = wday(start_time, label = TRUE)) %>%  #creates weekday field using wday()
  group_by(usertype, weekday) %>%  #groups by usertype and weekday
  summarise(number_of_rides = n()                       #calculates the number of rides and average duration 
            ,average_duration = mean(ride_length)) %>%      # calculates the average duration
  arrange(usertype, weekday)                                # sorts

# Let's visualize the number of rides by rider type
all_trips_v2 %>% 
  mutate(weekday = wday(start_time, label = TRUE)) %>% 
  group_by(usertype, weekday) %>% 
  summarise(number_of_rides = n()
            ,average_duration = mean(ride_length)) %>% 
  arrange(usertype, weekday)  %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = weekday, y = number_of_rides, fill = usertype)) +
  geom_col(position = "dodge")
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'usertype'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

# Let's create a visualization for average duration

            ,average_duration = mean(ride_length)) %>%
